# UI Overhaul Phase 2

Fix tab lag, SearchableCombo flash, missing Save Config, and layout balance. Inspired by AZ-Labs reference design.

## Root Cause Analysis

| Problem | Root Cause | Fix |
|---|---|---|
| Tab switch lag/flicker | `CTkTabview` redraws on switch | Replace with manual frame show/hide |
| SearchableCombo flash | `CTkToplevel` creates new window each time | Reuse window, defer show |
| Product tab no Save Config | Simply missing | Add Save/Load config |
| Layout unbalanced | Rigid grid weights | Rebalance with LabelFrame sections |

## Proposed Changes

### Fix 1: Tab Switch Lag

#### [MODIFY] [main_window.py](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/1.Prompt_Image/1.Prompt_Image/ui/main_window.py)

Replace `CTkTabview` with simple button-based tab bar + frame show/hide:
- Build both tab frames at startup, pack them into same container
- Only one visible at a time (`pack_forget` / `pack`)
- Custom tab bar with `CTkSegmentedButton` for instant switching
- No animation = no flicker

---

### Fix 2: SearchableCombo Flash

#### [MODIFY] [searchable_combo.py](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/1.Prompt_Image/1.Prompt_Image/ui/searchable_combo.py)

- **Withdraw** dropdown window instead of destroying it
- Only create `CTkToplevel` once, reuse it
- Use `withdraw()`/`deiconify()` to hide/show

---

### Fix 3: Product Tab Save Config

#### [MODIFY] [product_tab.py](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/1.Prompt_Image/1.Prompt_Image/ui/product_tab.py)

- Add [_save_config()](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/1.Prompt_Image/1.Prompt_Image/ui/config_section.py#154-167) / [_load_config()](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/1.Prompt_Image/1.Prompt_Image/ui/config_section.py#232-254) methods (mirror config_section.py)
- Save: style, output_dir, tier, count, threads, constraints
- Load on init
- Add "Save Config" button in config bar

---

### Fix 4: Layout — Bordered Sections (like AZ-Labs)

#### [MODIFY] [config_section.py](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/1.Prompt_Image/1.Prompt_Image/ui/config_section.py)

